00:49.124 --> 00:51.091
Oh, hello.

00:51.143 --> 00:52.692
- I was just...
- Working.

00:52.728 --> 00:55.228
I see that,
but it's 7:30 in the morning.

00:55.263 --> 00:57.197
What are you doing here
so early?

00:57.199 --> 00:59.899
I like to get in
before the chaos starts.

00:59.935 --> 01:01.468
Tell you the truth,
I was under the impression

01:01.503 --> 01:03.636
that you wouldn't get in
till much later.

01:03.672 --> 01:05.071
I wanted to get a jump
on the day.

01:05.107 --> 01:07.874
Then maybe you should get
a jump on this.

01:07.909 --> 01:09.809
Why am I paying
Louis's laundry bill?

01:09.845 --> 01:10.944
Because if you pay it,

01:10.979 --> 01:12.712
he won't know
that we triple-starched

01:12.748 --> 01:13.780
all of his shirts.

01:13.815 --> 01:15.215
- We?
- Yes, we.

01:15.250 --> 01:17.450
He came after us.
We're coming after him.

01:17.486 --> 01:19.152
Did you think
I wouldn't have your back?

01:19.187 --> 01:20.187
You want the truth?

01:20.222 --> 01:21.588
I thought
you'd be asking for a raise

01:21.623 --> 01:22.956
after seeing
how much I make.

01:22.991 --> 01:24.524
I didn't look
at how much you make.

01:24.559 --> 01:25.759
And as far as I'm concerned,

01:25.794 --> 01:27.994
anyone who did
should be fired.

01:28.029 --> 01:29.479
You're all right, Gretchen.

01:29.531 --> 01:30.864
But for the time being,

01:30.899 --> 01:33.183
don't play any more jokes
on Louis.

01:33.218 --> 01:34.567
Mind if I ask why?

01:34.603 --> 01:35.969
Because I only play jokes
on people

01:36.004 --> 01:37.570
to express my affection
for them,

01:37.606 --> 01:41.107
and right now I have
no affection for Louis Litt.

01:43.011 --> 01:45.211
Looks like I got here
just in time.

01:45.213 --> 01:46.646
And why is that?

01:46.648 --> 01:47.914
Because I'm going
to ask you to do something

01:47.949 --> 01:49.215
you're not going
to want to do,

01:49.251 --> 01:50.650
only this time
you're going to do it.

01:50.652 --> 01:52.118
What didn't I do last time?

01:52.154 --> 01:55.188
I told you to apologize
to Louis.

01:55.223 --> 01:57.791
And I did, right before
he held hands with Jack Soloff

01:57.826 --> 01:59.976
and cut my earnings
in front of the entire firm.

02:00.011 --> 02:01.578
And if you hadn't have been
such a dick to Jack

02:01.613 --> 02:02.729
in the first place,

02:02.764 --> 02:04.497
Louis would have had
nowhere to go.

02:04.533 --> 02:06.099
This isn't about Louis,
is it?

02:06.134 --> 02:07.200
No, it isn't.

02:07.235 --> 02:08.701
I want you to bury
the hatchet with Jack.

02:08.737 --> 02:10.036
You mean you want me
to kiss his ass.

02:10.071 --> 02:11.471
I mean I want you
to figure out a way

02:11.506 --> 02:13.773
to make peace with a partner
whose influence is on the rise.

02:13.809 --> 02:15.041
That's kissing his ass.

02:15.043 --> 02:16.342
Well, if that's how
you want to look at it,

02:16.378 --> 02:18.845
then pucker up,
because that man is a threat,

02:18.880 --> 02:20.213
and he's aligned with Louis,

02:20.248 --> 02:22.682
and I am in no mood
for a power struggle.

02:31.993 --> 02:33.443
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:33.495 --> 02:34.944
I didn't hear
you leave today.

02:34.996 --> 02:36.596
That's because I left
at 5:00 in the morning,

02:36.631 --> 02:38.147
trying to get an early start
on this case.

02:38.183 --> 02:39.949
Mm.

02:39.985 --> 02:41.868
Uh, about that...

02:41.870 --> 02:43.536
I didn't want to say
anything last night

02:43.572 --> 02:45.171
because you were
so excited--

02:45.207 --> 02:47.941
But you're worried about me
working with your father.

02:47.976 --> 02:49.309
- Yes.
- Hmm.

02:49.344 --> 02:51.144
Mike, you're the two most
important men in my life.

02:51.179 --> 02:53.947
Neither of you back down
from a fight,

02:53.982 --> 02:55.548
and I'm just--

02:55.584 --> 02:57.851
I'm afraid you're gonna
end up hating each other.

03:01.189 --> 03:02.755
Rachel, do you hate
your father?

03:02.791 --> 03:04.657
Of course not.
I love my dad.

03:04.693 --> 03:07.026
And don't you have conflicts
with him all the time?

03:07.062 --> 03:09.779
Yes, I do,
but it's different.

03:09.814 --> 03:11.197
He's my family.

03:11.233 --> 03:13.333
Yeah, he's gonna be
my family too.

03:13.368 --> 03:15.018
And if I'm lucky,
I'm gonna fight with him

03:15.070 --> 03:17.036
about a lot of things
over the years.

03:17.072 --> 03:18.438
So why not start with a fight

03:18.473 --> 03:20.106
where we're both
on the same side?

03:20.141 --> 03:23.710
Okay, I trust you.

03:23.745 --> 03:25.812
Good.

03:25.847 --> 03:29.015
[upbeat music]

03:32.020 --> 03:33.536
Jessica, you have a minute?

03:33.572 --> 03:35.154
I do if you're here
to tell me

03:35.190 --> 03:36.756
why Robert Zane
is sitting in the lobby

03:36.791 --> 03:38.291
with an appointment
to see you.

03:38.326 --> 03:39.792
'Cause I'm pretty sure
he's not taking time

03:39.828 --> 03:41.694
out of his busy morning
to talk about centerpieces.

03:41.730 --> 03:43.763
No, he's not.

03:43.798 --> 03:47.867
He is here to co-counsel
the Kelton case.

03:47.903 --> 03:50.136
You mean the case
I explicitly told you to drop?

03:50.171 --> 03:52.872
I mean the case that you said
would cost a fortune to fund

03:52.874 --> 03:54.974
and you didn't wanna lay out
that kind of money for.

03:55.010 --> 03:57.043
I didn't want to lay it out
because this case is a loser.

03:57.095 --> 03:58.344
And I'm telling you
it's not.

03:58.396 --> 04:00.747
And even if it is,
I just took away our downside.

04:00.782 --> 04:03.416
By going behind my back
to our biggest competitor.

04:03.451 --> 04:05.184
Are you telling me that
you're scared of Robert Zane?

04:05.220 --> 04:06.719
I'd be a fool if I wasn't.

04:06.755 --> 04:08.388
And you're a fool
if you're not.

04:08.423 --> 04:09.689
We let that man
into our house,

04:09.724 --> 04:10.723
there's no telling
what he'll do.

04:10.759 --> 04:11.791
You know what, Jessica?

04:11.826 --> 04:12.892
If Harvey had done this,
you'd be pissed,

04:12.928 --> 04:13.860
but you'd let him
do it anyway.

04:13.895 --> 04:15.295
And you may be
as cocky as him,

04:15.330 --> 04:18.831
but you are not Harvey.

04:18.867 --> 04:21.184
No, you're right.
I'm sorry.

04:21.236 --> 04:22.535
I guess I'll just
go tell Robert

04:22.570 --> 04:24.487
that we won't be working
together on this after all.

04:24.539 --> 04:27.006
You know damn well
if we tell him that now,

04:27.008 --> 04:29.609
I look weak.

04:29.661 --> 04:31.311
So maybe I am
as good as Harvey.

04:31.346 --> 04:33.479
Well, sometimes
that's not a good thing.

04:34.950 --> 04:36.449
Where are you going?

04:36.501 --> 04:38.468
To get
some goddamn strength back.

04:41.222 --> 04:42.822
Then go ahead and do it.

04:42.874 --> 04:44.173
I won't just take you
to the woodshed.

04:44.209 --> 04:46.659
I'll leave you there, dead.

04:48.897 --> 04:50.730
Well, looks like you're
making yourself comfortable

04:50.732 --> 04:52.465
in my offices.

04:52.500 --> 04:54.567
About as comfortable
as possible in these chairs.

04:54.602 --> 04:56.369
You ever hear
of lumbar support?

04:56.404 --> 04:59.105
I get it.
You like stodgy and functional.

04:59.140 --> 05:02.342
But these are my chairs,
just like this is my case.

05:02.377 --> 05:04.677
What exactly are you
doing here, Jessica?

05:04.713 --> 05:05.713
I'm here to tell you

05:05.714 --> 05:06.913
we're taking
half the contingency.

05:06.948 --> 05:08.848
And I'm here to respond.
I'm giving you 1/3.

05:08.883 --> 05:10.149
We brought this case to you.

05:10.185 --> 05:11.985
After you found it in a box
crying for its mama.

05:12.020 --> 05:13.553
Plus, I'm footing the bill,

05:13.588 --> 05:15.755
which means
this fee discussion is over.

05:15.790 --> 05:18.891
Well, this fee discussion
may be over,

05:18.927 --> 05:23.262
but the power discussion
is just getting started.

05:23.298 --> 05:25.865
You don't give a shit
about the money, do you?

05:25.900 --> 05:27.467
On this particular case,

05:27.502 --> 05:29.902
all I give a shit about
is keeping you in check.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.205
Which means, for the duration
of this matter,

05:32.240 --> 05:34.574
you will be treating
Mike Ross like a partner.

05:34.609 --> 05:36.109
Oh, you gotta
be kidding me.

05:36.144 --> 05:37.677
That boy barely shaves.

05:37.712 --> 05:38.878
I don't care
if he's still in diapers.

05:38.913 --> 05:40.213
He's representing my firm,

05:40.248 --> 05:41.714
which means
he's representing me.

05:41.750 --> 05:44.851
You look at him,
you see me.

05:44.886 --> 05:46.986
You're asking
for a hell of a lot.

05:47.022 --> 05:48.221
Then take your wingtips
off my table

05:48.256 --> 05:49.256
and walk 'em
out the door,

05:49.290 --> 05:50.923
because this is my case

05:50.959 --> 05:53.079
and you either do it my way
or you don't do it at all.

05:54.929 --> 05:56.729
Mm.

05:58.700 --> 06:01.601
I love you.

06:01.636 --> 06:05.238
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:05.240 --> 06:08.574
♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:08.626 --> 06:11.794
♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:11.830 --> 06:15.415
♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:15.417 --> 06:18.301
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪

06:18.336 --> 06:22.305
♪ Me and Missy is
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:22.340 --> 06:23.790
♪ All right ♪

06:23.825 --> 06:25.345
♪ All step back,
I'm 'bout to dance ♪

